  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Epure BOT Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Chinas wastewater sector is experiencing unprecedented growth, as major cities seek to meet national wastewater treatment standards. In order to raise funds and mobilize private sector expertise to meet the huge investment demands effectively, the Chinese government has sought private sector participation in the sector from the early part of this decade. In this context, the Build-Operate-Transfer (BOT) has become an important approach in bringing in much needed investment into the wastewater sector.

Epure International Ltd.  (Epure) provides water and wastewater treatment solutions in China. It started its wastewater business in late 2008 and since then, it has won several BOT concessions with total treatment capacity of 280,000 tons/day. The proposed project will provide financing support to the BOT projects.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will have high development impact via IFCs support of a key private player to address wastewater related environmental pollution problems. This becomes even more compelling as several of the BOT projects are in frontier regions of China. Success of this project will demonstrate that private enterprises in the wastewater sector can be profitable and would help attract capital flows into this critical sector.</narrative>
  </description>
